You could say 'well she's only critiquing the one movie that came out,' but it doesn't change that it would be inaccurate to say such things about the characters when so much significant character development happens in the later films

By far the majority is male-centric? Do you even read books? These aren't just 'a couple' of examples otherwise, these are some of the most popular books out there. What you're displaying is exactly why there are so many feminists and SJW who believe in this <b> patriarchy,</b> androcentric nonsense: they selective look at every book/movie/TV series that can be twisted in some hair-splitting way into being sexist and claim it's evidence of a social imbalance, yet any and every female dominated series is downplayed or selectively ignored

